  </td>
  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>You have no direct control over most of your
  empire&#8217;s economic activity. Instead your influence is limited to ma=
intaining
  safe trade routes for your empire. By protecting trade to your colonies y=
ou
  help them to grow and increase the wealth that they generate.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>As explained in the topic &#8220;Your Empire&#8221;,=
 you
  only control the &#8220;State&#8221; portion of your empire. Your subject=
s in
  the &#8220;Private&#8221; part of your empire automatically go about their
  business, generating wealth.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>A summary of your empire&#8217;s State and Private
  economies are displayed in the Empire Summary Screen (F6).</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The various types of income and expenses of your Sta=
te
  economy are explained below.</p>
  <h2>Income</h2>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_0" o=
:spid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
   type=3D"#_x0000_t75" alt=3D"econ.png" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-=
left:159pt;
   margin-top:256.85pt;width:210.2pt;height:124.65pt;z-index:251658240;
   visibility:visible;mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;
   mso-height-percent:0;mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;
   mso-wrap-distance-right:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;
   mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;
   mso-position-vertical:absolute;mso-position-vertical-relative:text;
   mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;mso-width-relative:page;
   mso-height-relative:page'>
   <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_Economy_files/image002.png" o:title=3D"=
econ"/>
   <w:wrap type=3D"square" side=3D"left"/>
  </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D280 height=3D166
  src=3D"GameConcepts_Economy_files/image003.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12
  alt=3Decon.png v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_0"><![endif]>Your empire&#8217;s=
 state
  economy is fuelled by four major sources of income:</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Colony Tax Revenue</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-lis=
t:l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Private Ship Construction</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-lis=
t:l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Trade Transaction Fees</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:=
l0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Free Trade Agreements</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Each of these revenue sources are explained in detail
  below.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Colony Tax =
Revenue:</b>
  You can directly adjust colony tax rates. This allows you to collect more
  revenue from each colony. However, the higher you raise taxes, the more
  evasion there will be &#8211; some of your citizens will find ways to avo=
id
  paying. Also, higher taxes lower colony happiness and wealth production.<=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Ship Constr=
uction:</b>
  Expanding your empire with new colonies stimulates demand for new freight=
ers
  and mining ships from your private citizens. These ship purchases at your
  construction yards add more money to your state economy.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Trade Trans=
action
  Fees:</b> Fees are charged on each transaction at your space ports and mi=
ning
  stations, earning income for your empire. Thus it is important to ensure =
free
  and safe trade to these locations. You should patrol your space ports and
  mining stations and chase away any threats such as pirates, aggressive sp=
ace
  creatures or enemy empires.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Free Trade
  Agreements:</b> You gain income when you form Free Trade Agreements with
  other empires. In this situation a percentage of the entire trade volume
  between the two empires is earned as bonus income by each empire. Over ti=
me
  the bonus percentage grows until it reaches a maximum limit.</p>
  <h2>Expenses</h2>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The state economy of your empire has three major exp=
enses:</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Maintenance costs for ships and bases</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-lis=
t:l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Maintenance costs for troops</p>
  <p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:=
l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
  style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-=
family:
  Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt=
 "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  </span></span></span><![endif]>Maintenance costs for intelligence agents<=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Maintenance costs can be controlled by carefully bal=
ancing
  the number of ships, troops and agents your empire uses. Only build ships
  that you need. Only recruit troops and agents that you need.</p>
